# ── R-23 (2026-06-08): NTH DAO workspace identity material ──
# These files are the workspace's Ed25519 keypair, mandate ledger,
# contact book, and audit log. They MUST NEVER be committed:
#
#   * .nth/identity.json contains the PRIVATE KEY in plaintext. A
#     single push to a public repo exposes the workspace's permanent
#     signing identity - any attacker can then sign mandates as the
#     owner, forge endorsements, and impersonate the operator on the
#     LAN.
#   * team.json, team_contacts/, team_trust/, team_marketplace/ all
#     contain participant identities, balances, and audit history
#     that are private to the workspace operator.
#   * console.token authenticates dashboard calls; leaking it gives
#     anyone with HTTP access to the running console full control.
#
# Patterns are deliberately broad (**/ glob) because the workspace
# directory is operator-configurable via NTH_WORKSPACE - it may live
# at the repo root, in a subdirectory, or under a sibling path the
# operator added to the working tree.
.nth/
**/.nth/
**/identity.json
**/team.json
**/team_contacts/
**/team_marketplace/
console.token
**/console.token
